<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">binding and finishing</a>, the untrimmed, usually folded edges of a <a title="Signature" href="Signature">signature</a> prior to trimming, not including the <a title="Binding Edge" href="Binding_Edge">binding edge</a>. The fold at the top of a signature is known as the <a title="Head Bolt" href="Head_Bolt">head bolt</a>. Uncut signature folds are called <a title="Closed Bolts" href="Closed_Bolts">closed bolts</a>. Roughly trimmed edges are called <a title="Open Bolts" href="Open_Bolts">open bolts</a>. Both open and closed bolts require complete trimming at the end of the binding process. 
</p>
